Trim the zucchini and cut into cubes. Cube the tomatoes eliminating most of the seeds. In a skillet over medium-high heat, add the butter and olive oil. Add the onion, celery, bell peppers and garlic. Saute for about 2 minutes. Add the zucchini, tomatoes, Tabasco and herbs. Saute until zucchini are tender. Taste test and add salt pepper or more Tabasco as desired.